name: LEGOLAND
description: A LEGO-themed family theme park resort in Winter Haven (near Orlando), featuring rides, shows, water park, and 3 LEGOLAND Hotels.

name: EPCOT - Walt Disney World Resort
description: A 25,000-acre entertainment resort southwest of Orlando, home to four theme parks (Magic Kingdom, EPCOT, Studios, Animal Kingdom), two water parks, and Disney Springs.

name: Busch Gardens
description: A 335-acre African-themed animal park in Tampa, Florida​:contentReference[oaicite:9]{index=9} with roller coasters and wildlife exhibits.

name: SeaWorld
description: An animal-themed marine park and entertainment complex in Orlando​:contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}, featuring marine life shows, thrill rides, and seasonal festivals.

name: Universal Orlando Resort
description: A 1,291-acre theme park and entertainment resort in Orlando, including Universal Studios Florida, Islands of Adventure, Volcano Bay, CityWalk and on-site hotels​:contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}.

name: Disney Springs
description: Disney Springs is an outdoor shopping, dining, and entertainment complex at the Walt Disney World Resort

name: ICON Park Orlando
description: A 20-acre open-air entertainment complex on I-Drive (Downtown Orlando), featuring The Wheel, Madame Tussauds, SEA LIFE aquarium, shops and restaurants.
